- How would you detect and mitigate poisoned shares in real time?

## Why This Is Asked
Explains how to add observability and robust failure handling in a real API, a common beginner hurdle as systems scale.

## Key Concepts
- Distributed tracing, metrics, circuit breakers
- Idempotency and retry strategies
- Canary rollout and failover testing

## Code Example
```javascript
// Lightweight circuit-breaker sketch
class CircuitBreaker {
  constructor(threshold=5, windowMs=60000) { this.failures=0; this.threshold=threshold; this.open=false; }
  recordFailure(){ this.failures++; if(this.failures>this.threshold){ this.open=true; setTimeout(()=>{ this.open=false; this.failures=0; }, 30000);} }
  canProceed(){ return !this.open; }
}
```

## Follow-up Questions
- How would you adapt the observability plan for a serverless environment?
- What would you monitor to detect data drift affecting cca_score?

## Why This Is Asked

Tests understanding of privacy-preserving experimentation at an API boundary and how to build deterministic, auditable feature variants into an existing compute API.

## Key Concepts

- Deterministic hashing (HMAC) for stable variant assignment
- Data masking (user_id_masked) to protect PII
- Experiment design (experiment_id, variant) and minimal integration with cca_score
- API design, observability, and simple test strategies

## Code Example

```javascript
const crypto = require('crypto');
function variantFor(userId, experimentId, secret){
  const hash = crypto.createHmac('sha256', secret).update(userId + '-' + experimentId).digest('hex');
  const n = parseInt(hash.slice(0, 8), 16);
  return (n % 2 === 0) ? 'A' : 'B';
}
```

## Follow-up Questions

- How would you extend to more than two variants while preserving determinism?
- How would you validate fairness and detect potential leakage across experiments?

## Why This Is Asked

