## Why This Is Asked
This question evaluates your ability to design a privacy-preserving ABAC layer that controls access to encrypted CCA score shares without revealing plaintext data. It tests understanding of dynamic admin access, revocation mechanisms, auditability, and system design at scale.

## Key Concepts
- ABAC attributes: tenant_id, region, role, expiry
- Token-based access without decryption
- Immutable audit logs with tamper-evident provenance
- Key management with per-tenant keys
- Revocation and expiry propagation

## Code Example
```javascript
function evaluatePolicy(attrs, action) {
  const now = Date.now();

  if (attrs.expiry < now) return { allowed: false, reason: 'expired' };
  if (!attrs.tenant_id || !attrs.region) return { allowed: false, reason: 'missing attributes' };

  const policy = getPolicy(attrs.policy_id);
  if (!policy) return { allowed: false, reason: 'policy not found' };

  const regionMatch = policy.regions.includes(attrs.region);
  const roleMatch = policy.roles.includes(attrs.role);

  return { allowed: regionMatch && roleMatch, reason: regionMatch && roleMatch ? 'ok' : 'attribute mismatch' };
}

function revokeAccess(policyId, reason) {
  const policy = getPolicy(policyId);
  policy.revoked = true;
  policy.revocationReason = reason;
  publishRevocationEvent(policyId);
}
```

## Why This Is Asked

